comments: Coulibaly (WAS) initiates contact across Williams' (CHA) left arm during the rebound.
Coulibaly (WAS) brings his hands forward toward Ball's (CHA) body, and marginal contact occurs as Ball receives the inbound.
Williams (CHA) establishes himself in Coulibaly's (WAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Williams (CHA) establishes himself in Coulibaly's (WAS) path and absorbs the upper-body contact during the pick.
Gafford (WAS) is firming up over his left foot and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the pick on Miller (CHA).
Coulibaly (WAS) is moving forward as Ball (CHA) changes direction during the drive and marginal body contact occurs when they come together.
Ball (CHA) gathers the ball by bringing his left hand underneath it and takes two legal steps before releasing the pass.
Kuzma (WAS) initiates contact across Williams' (CHA) left arm during the dunk attempt, which is subsequently affected.
Ball (CHA) cleanly dislodges the ball away from Poole (WAS) prior to incidental contact occurring with Poole's front during the rebound.
Bridges (CHA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Poole (WAS) in transition.

Coulibaly (WAS) is late to the spot and does not maintain a legal guarding position as Bridges (CHA) slips to his side during the driving shot attempt, which is subsequently altered as a result of the contact.
Bridges (CHA) and Gafford (WAS) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs as Gafford rolls into the lane following the expiration of the pick.
Kuzma (WAS) goes to, not through, Williams' (CHA) space and marginal contact occurs after Kuzma picks up his dribble in the post.
Ball (CHA) brings his off-arm toward Coulibaly's (WAS) side and releases away without applying any force as Ball slows his momentum on the wing.
Gafford (WAS) establishes himself in Bridges' (CHA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Bridges' (CHA) left hand brushes Kuzma's (WAS) left side and marginal contact occurs as Kuzma starts his upward shooting motion.
Miller (CHA) makes clean contact with the ball and back-taps it away from Gafford (WAS) prior to incidental body contact occurring during the rebound.
Williams (CHA) maintains a rested forearm on Gafford's (WAS) back and marginal contact occurs simultaneously with the incidental body contact between Miller (CHA) and Gafford.
Poole (WAS) commits a take foul on Williams (CHA). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Ball (CHA) jumps vertically and incidental body contact occurs with Kuzma's (WAS) left side after his gather.
Kuzma (WAS) brings an extended right hand toward Bridges (CHA) and marginal contact occurs as Kuzma releases away to receive the inbound.
Kuzma (WAS) commits a take foul on Bridges (CHA).
Ball (CHA) grasps and then quickly releases Jones' (WAS) jersey off-ball.
Gafford (WAS) extends outward prior to marginal contact occurring with Ball (CHA) as Ball spins underneath the screen.
Bridges (CHA) releases the inbound within five seconds.
Ball (CHA) receives the ball and lifts and replaces his pivot foot before starting his dribble.
Coulibaly (WAS) extends and initiates body contact that affects Ball's (CHA) SQBR along the sideline.
Miller (CHA) maintains a rested left hand on Poole's (WAS) side and releases away as marginal contact occurs when Poole cuts toward the wing.
Bridges (CHA) legally contests Kuzma's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
